  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7024.46 sitting right at the massive +106.7B GEX wall at 7025, dealers are aggressively selling into this level to hedge their long gamma positions, creating strong resistance. The PIN regime with a high GEX flip at 6860 means dealers will continue to fade any upside momentum here and provide buying support on dips, particularly around the 7000 level (+10.9B GEX). The gex_surge event combined with spot pinned at max positive gamma suggests we're hitting peak resistance where dealer selling pressure is most intense.\n\nKey levels: 7025 (max dealer selling), 7000 (secondary support), and 6860 (regime flip point).\n\n**Bottom line:** expect the market to stall and reverse lower from current levels due to heavy dealer selling pressure.",
